Ruben Loftus-Cheek is all set to be handed his Chelsea debut on Wednesday night during their dead-rubber against Sporting Lisbon. 

The 18-year-old has yet to feature for the Blues but manager Jose Mourinho confirmed that he will be given a chance in the Champions League. 

'I am so happy to give the kids a chance. He is an English player, 18, completely made in Chelsea. If he succeeds it's good,' Mourinho said. 

